Trying to use Project Fi while traveling in Eastern Europe, but for some reason data didn't work. After talking to Project Fi support for 3 hours I downloaded this app.  After running this app and trying every possible thing using this app. Finally, after a repair and phone restart the data started to work.  Now, 3 weeks later, the problem has returned, still not sure how to really fix it. If there were better instructions or a walkthrough for diagnosing issues, that would help.  Update: The developer has tried to help, but this app is more designed for US based codes, not international. I'll update again if and when I solve my international problems. Update2: I figured it out! Data now works again. It seems that I just need to make sure I use Vivacom and not Telenor BG.  Steps  1. Switch to 3G 2. Enable WiFi 3. Switch to Vivacom 4. Disable WiFi to verify that data works.  It is too bad I cannot get 4G, but 3G is better than nothing :)
replyContent: Sorry for the troubles! Unfortunately the dialer codes used in this app that are listened for by the main Project Fi app are focused on US carrier switching - this is a limit imposed by the main Project Fi app and I am not aware of international-based ones. Awesome that you were able to figure out what was going on, and thanks for the update!
